        <svcproc id="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        turn the engine off, set the parking brake and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the front axle engagement sensor port (Figure 1 or Figure 2) and remove the pipe
                    plug.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply Loctite 242 thread sealant to the engagement sensor threads, install and tighten
                    to 200 to 258 Lbf-ft (270 to 350 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the chassis harness connector. Connect the sensor to the chassis harness.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the ignition switch in the ON position, shift the transfer case to all wheel drive
                    and verify the indicator light is ON.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure wiring to keep it away from the transfer case output yoke.</para>
            </step1>
